    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_399010757" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/399010757" />
    <a title="Patricia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12116516-patricia"><img alt="Patricia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1495778044p2/12116516.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/399010757?book_show_action=true">Aug 23, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Patricia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Patricia" href="/user/show/12116516-patricia">Patricia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12116516-patricia?shelf=2012">2012</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer399010757" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16383442297211383387">A very poignant book during this time of war. The story is based on the Greek classic, Antigone and references to this work appear throughout the book. A woman arrives at a remote outpost in Khandahar Afghanistan to claim and bury her brother. After a devastating attack on the outpost, the troops do not know whether to believe this woman is there in peace or if she a spy leading a future attack or a suicide bomber. The various members of the platoon tell their story sparked by this woman&apos;s appea</span>
  <span id="freeText16383442297211383387" style="display:none">A very poignant book during this time of war. The story is based on the Greek classic, Antigone and references to this work appear throughout the book. A woman arrives at a remote outpost in Khandahar Afghanistan to claim and bury her brother. After a devastating attack on the outpost, the troops do not know whether to believe this woman is there in peace or if she a spy leading a future attack or a suicide bomber. The various members of the platoon tell their story sparked by this woman's appearance. In the end, no one wins. </span>
  <a data-text-id="16383442297211383387" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

