<div id="review_313478155" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/313478155" />
    <a title="Richard" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8215326-richard"><img alt="Richard" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/313478155?book_show_action=true">Apr 16, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Richard" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Richard" href="/user/show/8215326-richard">Richard</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer313478155" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7542181691472399751">Very reminiscent of Tim O&apos;Brien: A non-linear plot weaving the surreal memories and fantasies of the soldiers with the troubling and often brutal realtities of their circumstances, all framed within a life or death decision pertaining to an Afghan civilian. As Sassoon wrote, and as O&apos;Brien echoed, &quot;Soldiers are dreamers&quot;, and this book captures their wistful innocence, desparate frustration, and capacity for cruelty. Solid read.</span>
  <span id="freeText7542181691472399751" style="display:none">Very reminiscent of Tim O'Brien: A non-linear plot weaving the surreal memories and fantasies of the soldiers with the troubling and often brutal realtities of their circumstances, all framed within a life or death decision pertaining to an Afghan civilian. As Sassoon wrote, and as O'Brien echoed, "Soldiers are dreamers", and this book captures their wistful innocence, desparate frustration, and capacity for cruelty. Solid read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7542181691472399751" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


